OS OPER SET <b>GLOBAL</b>
Usage: /msg Operserv SET <Oper> <b>GLOBAL</b> [ON|OFF]
Usage: /os SET <Oper> <b>GLOBAL</b> [ON|OFF]
-
-
With <b>GLOBAL</b>, you can set whether the specified oper is allowed to use the GLOBAL command. 
Only Services Administrators with default access to Operserv can use this command.   
-      
-
- Example
-
- OPER SET foo <b>GLOBAL ON</b> 
- OPER SET foo <b>GLOBAL OFF</b>
- 
-
- OPER SET <b>GLOBAL</b> - End of help